WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.023 --> 00:00:02.305
(Epic theme playing)

2
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

3
00:01:02.719 --> 00:01:05.515
(Vocalizing)

4
00:01:14.675 --> 00:01:17.459
<font color=#FF00FF>*HOUSE OF DRAGON*</font> 
<font color=#00FF00>Season 01  Episode 02</font>

5
00:01:17.544 --> 00:01:19.625
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"The Rogue Prince"</font>
Aired on: <font color="#00ffff">August 28. 2022.</font>

6
00:01:19.710 --> 00:01:22.335
(Tense music playing)

7
00:01:25.950 --> 00:01:28.519
(Water flowing)

8
00:01:31.848 --> 00:01:35.891
(Indistinct yelling)

9
00:01:37.919 --> 00:01:41.703
(Winces. groans)

10
00:01:42.140 --> 00:01:44.703
(People yelling)

11
00:01:46.941 --> 00:01:50.273
(Distant screaming)

12
00:01:50.406 --> 00:01:53.075
King Viserys: Ser Ryam was
a strong Lord Commander

13
00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:54.703
of the Kings guard.

14
00:01:55.527 --> 00:01:57.487
But he was ill for some time.

15
00:01:57.579 --> 00:01:59.070
He passed in peace. I hope.

16
00:01:59.155 --> 00:02:00.196
Grand Maester Mellos:
Yes. Your Grace.

17
00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:01.451
He was found to have passed

18
00:02:01.536 --> 00:02:03.305
gently in his sleep.

19
00:02:03.375 --> 00:02:06.360
His remains are being prepared
by the Silent Sisters.

20
00:02:06.445 --> 00:02:09.811
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

21
00:02:09.896 --> 00:02:14.036
would like to make haste in finding
Ser Ryam's replacement on the Kings guard.

22
00:02:14.121 --> 00:02:16.123
Ser Harrold We sterling:
Your Grace. My lords.

23
00:02:16.529 --> 00:02:19.620
The Kings guard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

24
00:02:20.747 --> 00:02:22.165
With the help of the Hand.

25
00:02:22.250 --> 00:02:24.550
I've invited a number of
fine candidates to court.

26
00:02:24.635 --> 00:02:26.512
All have passed fair trials.

27
00:02:26.940 --> 00:02:28.690
(Door opens)

28
00:02:30.371 --> 00:02:32.290
Four ships have now been lost.

29
00:02:32.375 --> 00:02:33.956
The last one was flying my banner.

30
00:02:34.616 --> 00:02:36.578
The Step stones have now
grown into a conflagration.

31
00:02:36.662 --> 00:02:39.026
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

32
00:02:39.111 --> 00:02:41.072
Ser Harrold We sterling:
If you've something to discuss.

33
00:02:41.157 --> 00:02:43.018
- Lord Corlys...
- I want to know what is to be done

34
00:02:43.103 --> 00:02:45.065
about my ships and my men.

35
00:02:45.150 --> 00:02:46.360
The Crown will compensate you

36
00:02:46.445 --> 00:02:48.572
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

37
00:02:48.657 --> 00:02:51.743
- to the men's families.
- I don't want compensation.

38
00:02:53.488 --> 00:02:55.865
I want to seize the Step stones by force

39
00:02:55.949 --> 00:02:57.346
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

40
00:02:57.431 --> 00:03:00.221
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

41
00:03:00.306 --> 00:03:03.017
These pirates are not the Free Cities.

42
00:03:03.102 --> 00:03:06.188
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

43
00:03:06.273 --> 00:03:08.108
In all of its history. my lord.

44
00:03:08.193 --> 00:03:10.042
the Seven Kingdoms have never entered

45
00:03:10.127 --> 00:03:11.837
open war with the Free Cities.

46
00:03:11.975 --> 00:03:13.602
Were that to happen.

47
00:03:13.687 --> 00:03:15.839
the losses would be incalculable.

48
00:03:19.898 --> 00:03:22.817
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

49
00:03:25.209 --> 00:03:27.719
The King's own brother has been allowed
to seize Dragons tone

50
00:03:27.804 --> 00:03:30.659
and fortify it with an army
of his gold cloaks.

51
00:03:30.744 --> 00:03:33.198
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

52
00:03:33.283 --> 00:03:35.244
without even a protest from The Crown.

53
00:03:35.329 --> 00:03:37.714
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

54
00:03:37.921 --> 00:03:41.851
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

55
00:03:44.561 --> 00:03:46.297
I have acted. Corlys.

56
00:03:47.181 --> 00:03:49.734
I've sent envoys to Pentos and Volantis

57
00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:52.445
to see if we might find common cause.

58
00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:55.195
Ships and men are at the ready.

59
00:03:55.938 --> 00:03:59.275
The Step stones will be settled
in time.

60
00:03:59.766 --> 00:04:01.935
You have dragon riders. father.

61
00:04:08.139 --> 00:04:09.223
Send us.

62
00:04:11.893 --> 00:04:13.557
(Soft chuckle)

63
00:04:13.848 --> 00:04:16.956
It isn't that simple. Rhaenyra.

64
00:04:17.041 --> 00:04:18.584
It would be a show of force.

65
00:04:19.166 --> 00:04:21.127
At least the Princess has a plan.

66
00:04:24.769 --> 00:04:27.313
- I only meant that we should at least...
- Perhaps.

67
00:04:27.481 --> 00:04:31.652
there's some better use
for the Princess's talents. Your Grace.

68
00:04:33.929 --> 00:04:35.978
King Viserys: Why don't you take
the Princess to see about the new

69
00:04:36.062 --> 00:04:38.227
Kings guard posting. Lord Commander?

70
00:04:39.537 --> 00:04:41.508
A fine idea. Your Grace.

71
00:04:42.934 --> 00:04:45.368
This knight will protect you as well.

72
00:04:45.453 --> 00:04:46.996
You should choose.

73
00:04:49.796 --> 00:04:51.119
(Scoffs)

74
00:04:55.865 --> 00:04:57.865
(Door opens)

75
00:05:03.212 --> 00:05:05.493
(Birds chirping)

76
00:05:06.692 --> 00:05:08.485
Harrold: Ser Desmond Car on.

77
00:05:08.726 --> 00:05:10.938
a fine knight. Princess.

78
00:05:11.023 --> 00:05:12.942
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

79
00:05:15.198 --> 00:05:16.783
Son of Ser Royce Car on.

80
00:05:16.868 --> 00:05:19.180
Ser Desmond has proved strong and steady

81
00:05:19.265 --> 00:05:22.024
in both the tourney lists and without.

82
00:05:22.259 --> 00:05:25.047
While traveling through the Kings wood
on his way to King's Landing.

83
00:05:25.132 --> 00:05:27.821
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

84
00:05:27.906 --> 00:05:29.032
to justice.

85
00:05:39.385 --> 00:05:42.415
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

86
00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:46.079
We thank you for your loyal
service to The Crown. ser.

87
00:05:46.186 --> 00:05:48.749
(Footsteps departing)

88
00:05:57.001 --> 00:05:58.633
Harrold: Ser Rymun Mallister.

89
00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:03.454
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister of Seagard.

90
00:06:03.837 --> 00:06:06.047
Winner of the melee at Cider Hall.

91
00:06:06.169 --> 00:06:08.964
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

92
00:06:09.126 --> 00:06:11.337
Ser Rymun was knighted at eight-and-ten.

93
00:06:11.422 --> 00:06:13.626
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

94
00:06:14.455 --> 00:06:16.282
Beyond capturing poachers.

95
00:06:16.367 --> 00:06:19.952
(City bells tolling)

96
00:06:24.178 --> 00:06:26.097
Harrold: Ser Criston Cole.

97
00:06:31.729 --> 00:06:34.227
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

98
00:06:36.704 --> 00:06:38.665
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

99
00:06:40.604 --> 00:06:42.415
You saw combat in the Storm lands.

100
00:06:42.823 --> 00:06:44.594
Dornish marches. Princess.

101
00:06:45.012 --> 00:06:48.140
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

102
00:06:49.212 --> 00:06:51.172
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

103
00:06:51.257 --> 00:06:53.110
two of the watchtowers along the Boneway.

104
00:06:58.349 --> 00:07:00.017
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

105
00:07:00.301 --> 00:07:03.618
Let's not be too hasty. Princess.

106
00:07:04.516 --> 00:07:07.603
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

107
00:07:07.688 --> 00:07:10.149
but houses such as Crakehall and Mallister

108
00:07:10.234 --> 00:07:12.376
are important allies of The Crown.

109
00:07:12.461 --> 00:07:15.446
Seagard. for instance.
is the realm's prime defense

110
00:07:15.531 --> 00:07:17.199
against reavers from the Iron Islands.

111
00:07:17.284 --> 00:07:18.827
Those men are tourney knights.

112
00:07:18.974 --> 00:07:22.071
My father should be defended by a man
who's known real combat.

113
00:07:23.837 --> 00:07:24.963
Should he not?

114
00:07:27.170 --> 00:07:29.005
Of course. Princess.

115
00:07:29.090 --> 00:07:31.634
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

116
00:07:35.085 --> 00:07:37.405
(City bells tolling)

117
00:07:39.588 --> 00:07:42.507
King Viserys: The Valyrian capital
was built into a volcano.

118
00:07:42.592 --> 00:07:44.093
much like Dragons tone.

119
00:07:44.851 --> 00:07:47.718
And the dragon lords.
the highest of the nobility.

120
00:07:47.811 --> 00:07:50.730
lived here. at the volcanic face.

121
00:07:50.815 --> 00:07:53.985
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

122
00:07:54.355 --> 00:07:56.149
And this was the Anogrion.

123
00:07:57.692 --> 00:07:59.820
Where the bloodmages worked their craft.

124
00:08:02.254 --> 00:08:04.464
It is truly wondrous what you've built.

125
00:08:04.745 --> 00:08:05.745
Oh no.

126
00:08:06.868 --> 00:08:10.126
I only pore over the histories
and provide the plans.

127
00:08:10.211 --> 00:08:12.505
The stonemasons built the structures.

128
00:08:13.055 --> 00:08:15.704
Do you believe that Westeros
can be another Valyria. Your Grace?

129
00:08:15.789 --> 00:08:17.958
That depends.
whether you speak of the Freehold

130
00:08:18.043 --> 00:08:19.962
at its height or at its fall.

131
00:08:21.175 --> 00:08:22.844
Over a thousand dragons.

132
00:08:22.929 --> 00:08:25.849
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

133
00:08:28.896 --> 00:08:31.815
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

134
00:08:32.498 --> 00:08:34.497
(Object breaks)
Seven Hells.

135
00:08:38.096 --> 00:08:40.096
(Birds cawing)

136
00:08:49.578 --> 00:08:51.329
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

137
00:08:51.955 --> 00:08:54.064
- What do you mean?
- Well. these days.

138
00:08:54.149 --> 00:08:56.236
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

139
00:08:56.321 --> 00:08:58.490
I think she might find it difficult

140
00:08:59.613 --> 00:09:01.532
to discuss personal matters.

141
00:09:03.182 --> 00:09:04.391
It will take time.

142
00:09:06.555 --> 00:09:08.390
It did when I lost mine own mother.

143
00:09:14.374 --> 00:09:16.293
I wish she would approach me.

144
00:09:17.852 --> 00:09:19.103
What if you went to her?

145
00:09:19.963 --> 00:09:21.757
There are times when I would rather face

146
00:09:21.842 --> 00:09:24.716
the Black Dread himself
than mine own daughter of 15.

147
00:09:24.801 --> 00:09:26.145
(Chuckles)

148
00:09:27.687 --> 00:09:30.606
I think she would open
herself to you if invited.

149
00:09:31.485 --> 00:09:34.624
You do have such an easy way about you.
Your Grace.

150
00:09:38.750 --> 00:09:41.711
You do not mention our talks to Rhaenyra.
do you?

151
00:09:43.804 --> 00:09:44.930
I just.

152
00:09:46.398 --> 00:09:48.483
I fear that she wouldn't understand them.

153
00:09:49.064 --> 00:09:50.607
No. Your Grace.

154
00:09:57.253 --> 00:09:59.526
(Seabirds cawing)

155
00:10:03.578 --> 00:10:06.171
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

156
00:10:06.262 --> 00:10:08.294
and already they tried
to marry my father off

157
00:10:08.379 --> 00:10:10.179
and replace me as heir.

158
00:10:10.358 --> 00:10:12.546
I know those men and how they plot

159
00:10:12.631 --> 00:10:15.515
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

160
00:10:15.647 --> 00:10:18.788
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

161
00:10:21.059 --> 00:10:23.093
What if your father were to remarry?

162
00:10:31.202 --> 00:10:32.874
Your father loves you.

163
00:10:39.028 --> 00:10:40.946
He chose you for his heir.

164
00:10:41.969 --> 00:10:44.513
He didn't choose me. He spurns Daemon.

165
00:11:01.171 --> 00:11:02.714
Kneel with me.

166
00:11:19.268 --> 00:11:21.439
I find this is a way to be with my mother.

167
00:11:23.370 --> 00:11:25.288
Here in the quiet of the Sept.

168
00:11:26.616 --> 00:11:28.159
I feel close to her.

169
00:11:33.195 --> 00:11:36.086
- I know it sounds foolish.
- I don't think it's foolish.

170
00:11:37.811 --> 00:11:39.947
- I don't.
- Good.

171
00:11:43.133 --> 00:11:45.052
Because I thought you might try.

172
00:11:48.105 --> 00:11:51.567
If not for me. then. perhaps for them.

173
00:11:52.705 --> 00:11:54.705
(Sighs)

174
00:12:16.071 --> 00:12:17.989
What do I say?

175
00:12:18.804 --> 00:12:20.347
Whatever you wish.

176
00:12:21.699 --> 00:12:23.573
It's only for you and the gods to know.

177
00:12:25.483 --> 00:12:27.870
(Poignant music playing)

178
00:12:44.844 --> 00:12:47.269
(Crying)

179
00:12:56.929 --> 00:13:00.099
I want him to see me as
more than his little girl.

180
00:13:02.525 --> 00:13:05.343
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

181
00:13:05.872 --> 00:13:07.528
(Rhaenyra chuckles)

182
00:13:09.734 --> 00:13:11.569
When I wish to talk with him.

183
00:13:12.495 --> 00:13:14.622
I know that I must make the effort.

184
00:13:18.305 --> 00:13:19.421
Thank you.

185
00:13:30.905 --> 00:13:32.782
Corlys Velaryon: Your Grace.

186
00:13:32.867 --> 00:13:34.347
King Viserys: I'm glad we could meet.

187
00:13:34.718 --> 00:13:36.303
I know tempers ran hot today.

188
00:13:36.473 --> 00:13:38.558
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

189
00:13:38.643 --> 00:13:40.187
between our houses.

190
00:13:40.329 --> 00:13:42.873
Rhaenys is my favorite cousin after all.

191
00:13:44.281 --> 00:13:47.242
I wish to apologize for the tenor

192
00:13:47.326 --> 00:13:49.619
at the Small Council today. Your Grace.

193
00:13:49.703 --> 00:13:51.601
It was not my intent to make offense.

194
00:13:52.377 --> 00:13:56.109
Your fleet is one of the realm's
most important assets. Lord Corlys.

195
00:13:56.530 --> 00:13:58.074
But you must understand.

196
00:13:58.159 --> 00:14:00.578
as King. it is my obligation to avoid war

197
00:14:00.663 --> 00:14:02.546
until such time it is unavoidable.

198
00:14:02.642 --> 00:14:04.804
None among us desire open war.

199
00:14:06.338 --> 00:14:08.590
Might I speak plainly. Your Grace?

200
00:14:09.852 --> 00:14:12.859
I always welcome the unfettered thoughts
of my council.

201
00:14:13.220 --> 00:14:17.343
I fear that the eyes of our enemies
are presently fixed on the Red Keep.

202
00:14:18.292 --> 00:14:19.609
The Queen has passed.

203
00:14:19.807 --> 00:14:21.893
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

204
00:14:21.978 --> 00:14:23.663
the first in its history.

205
00:14:23.748 --> 00:14:25.432
The King's brother. so disinherited.

206
00:14:25.517 --> 00:14:27.429
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragons tone

207
00:14:27.514 --> 00:14:29.057
without challenge.

208
00:14:29.726 --> 00:14:32.312
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

209
00:14:32.397 --> 00:14:34.524
in our most critical shipping lane.

210
00:14:35.687 --> 00:14:39.190
You paint such an aspirant portrait
of my reign. Lord Corlys.

211
00:14:39.275 --> 00:14:41.054
It is an honest one. cousin.

212
00:14:42.211 --> 00:14:45.256
At the moment. The Crown is perceived
as being vulnerable.

213
00:14:45.746 --> 00:14:47.665
And a blind incursion in the Step stones

214
00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:50.002
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

215
00:14:50.087 --> 00:14:53.491
Corlys: To elude a storm.
you can either sail into it.

216
00:14:53.576 --> 00:14:55.161
or around it.

217
00:14:55.246 --> 00:14:57.706
But you must never await its coming.

218
00:14:59.012 --> 00:15:01.765
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

219
00:15:02.238 --> 00:15:03.670
my lord?

220
00:15:05.616 --> 00:15:07.451
Join our families.

221
00:15:08.133 --> 00:15:09.759
Wed our daughter. Laena.

222
00:15:09.843 --> 00:15:12.882
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

223
00:15:12.967 --> 00:15:15.999
With the Targaryen dragons
and the Velaryon fleet bound in blood.

224
00:15:16.084 --> 00:15:17.544
you can show the realm

225
00:15:17.629 --> 00:15:19.952
that The Crown's strongest days are ahead.

226
00:15:20.226 --> 00:15:21.311
not behind.

227
00:15:21.714 --> 00:15:24.270
(Tense music playing)

228
00:15:26.023 --> 00:15:27.566
I must admit.

229
00:15:28.204 --> 00:15:30.123
I haven't given marriage much thought.

230
00:15:30.791 --> 00:15:33.085
It hasn't even been half a year
since Aemma passed.

231
00:15:33.170 --> 00:15:36.507
The realm expects you to take a new wife
soon or late. Your Grace.

232
00:15:36.592 --> 00:15:39.491
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

233
00:15:39.629 --> 00:15:42.757
You could not ask for
a stronger match than Laena.

234
00:15:42.842 --> 00:15:44.826
(Birds chirping)

235
00:16:09.503 --> 00:16:11.630
We haven't spoken much

236
00:16:14.314 --> 00:16:15.523
since.

237
00:16:18.792 --> 00:16:20.418
A regret of mine.

238
00:16:21.987 --> 00:16:24.937
We should be free to speak our minds
to one another.

239
00:16:25.525 --> 00:16:27.068
You can say whatever you'd like.

240
00:16:27.270 --> 00:16:28.780
You are the King.

241
00:16:29.394 --> 00:16:30.746
(Chuckles)

242
00:16:36.641 --> 00:16:40.148
I loved your mother very much.

243
00:16:43.654 --> 00:16:44.947
As did I.

244
00:16:50.750 --> 00:16:52.750
(Tapping on table)

245
00:16:55.228 --> 00:16:56.617
(Sighs)

246
00:17:00.547 --> 00:17:03.717
Ser Harrold provided
a fine field of tourney knights.

247
00:17:03.801 --> 00:17:04.927
Oh?

248
00:17:06.011 --> 00:17:07.637
But in questioning them.

249
00:17:07.722 --> 00:17:10.304
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

250
00:17:10.389 --> 00:17:12.516
with true battle experience.

251
00:17:13.011 --> 00:17:15.555
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kings guard.

252
00:17:20.794 --> 00:17:24.171
- Today at Small Council...
- Pay it no mind.

253
00:17:24.256 --> 00:17:27.050
- I thought I might have had some insight.
- You're young.

254
00:17:27.987 --> 00:17:29.113
You will learn.

255
00:17:52.851 --> 00:17:56.396
Mellos: This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

256
00:17:58.383 --> 00:18:00.656
The maggots will remove the dead flesh

257
00:18:00.741 --> 00:18:03.286
and hopefully stop the advance of the rot.

258
00:18:08.602 --> 00:18:11.023
I held an audience earlier today

259
00:18:11.108 --> 00:18:13.277
with Lord Corlys and Princess Rhaenys.

260
00:18:13.362 --> 00:18:15.804
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

261
00:18:15.889 --> 00:18:18.767
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

262
00:18:18.852 --> 00:18:20.770
He proposed a marriage.

263
00:18:21.959 --> 00:18:24.359
To whom. Your Grace?

264
00:18:24.986 --> 00:18:26.530
The Lady Laena.

265
00:18:27.144 --> 00:18:29.229
To combine the strength of our houses.

266
00:18:29.314 --> 00:18:32.343
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

267
00:18:32.428 --> 00:18:33.513
not behind.

268
00:18:33.598 --> 00:18:35.975
Lord Corlys has overreached. Your Grace.

269
00:18:36.647 --> 00:18:40.030
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

270
00:18:40.115 --> 00:18:42.826
That is what I'm doing. presently.

271
00:18:44.087 --> 00:18:47.632
So. what is your advice. dear Otto.

272
00:18:48.672 --> 00:18:50.366
Otto: The Lady Laena

273
00:18:51.159 --> 00:18:53.320
is young. Your Grace.

274
00:18:53.648 --> 00:18:56.860
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

275
00:18:56.945 --> 00:18:58.484
still linger. my King.

276
00:18:58.688 --> 00:19:01.804
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

277
00:19:01.889 --> 00:19:03.891
sealing the breach

278
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:06.854
and uniting the two great Valyrian houses

279
00:19:06.939 --> 00:19:10.023
would certainly signal unity
throughout the realm

280
00:19:10.257 --> 00:19:11.758
and beyond.

281
00:19:12.056 --> 00:19:14.433
The Grand Maester's reasoning is sound.

282
00:19:16.302 --> 00:19:18.096
I do fear what Rhaenyra might think.

283
00:19:18.181 --> 00:19:20.100
Mellos: What does it matter. Your Grace?

284
00:19:20.185 --> 00:19:22.351
Her mother has passed.

285
00:19:22.436 --> 00:19:24.814
Her father must propagate the royal line.

286
00:19:31.443 --> 00:19:35.364
I dearly loved my own lady wife.

287
00:19:36.255 --> 00:19:39.174
The pain of her passing still haunts me.

288
00:19:40.844 --> 00:19:42.762
And to be compelled to

289
00:19:43.850 --> 00:19:46.394
replace her for duty's sake.

290
00:19:47.927 --> 00:19:49.470
You are the King.

291
00:19:50.534 --> 00:19:52.452
But I do not envy you.

292
00:19:58.182 --> 00:20:00.182
(Birds chirping)

293
00:20:04.029 --> 00:20:05.747
(Insects buzzing)

294
00:20:19.997 --> 00:20:22.542
What was it like flying the Black Dread?

295
00:20:22.819 --> 00:20:25.697
You were Balerion's last rider.

296
00:20:25.923 --> 00:20:29.039
Only for a short time before he died.

297
00:20:29.159 --> 00:20:30.202
With Balerion

298
00:20:30.287 --> 00:20:32.873
died the last memory of Valyria of Old.

299
00:20:33.576 --> 00:20:35.328
But Vhagar still lives

300
00:20:35.679 --> 00:20:36.991
somewhere.

301
00:20:37.076 --> 00:20:39.416
- (King Viserys sighs)
- Bit too large for the Dragon pit.

302
00:20:39.782 --> 00:20:42.326
Some would say too large for our world.

303
00:20:43.255 --> 00:20:46.342
- Do you know where she nests?
- I'm sorry?

304
00:20:46.427 --> 00:20:48.360
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

305
00:20:48.445 --> 00:20:51.156
The Dragon keepers believe she made home

306
00:20:51.241 --> 00:20:53.281
somewhere on the coast of the Narrow Sea.

307
00:20:53.366 --> 00:20:56.211
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

308
00:20:56.848 --> 00:20:58.754
They say it is a sad thing.

309
00:20:59.119 --> 00:21:00.512
(King Viserys sighs)

310
00:21:00.719 --> 00:21:02.891
I imagine even dragons get lonely.

311
00:21:07.144 --> 00:21:08.395
Your Grace.

312
00:21:09.381 --> 00:21:11.341
it would be a great honor

313
00:21:11.426 --> 00:21:15.297
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

314
00:21:15.484 --> 00:21:17.086
I would give you many children

315
00:21:17.171 --> 00:21:18.821
of pure Valyrian blood

316
00:21:18.906 --> 00:21:20.930
so that we might strengthen the royal line

317
00:21:21.015 --> 00:21:22.383
and the realm.

318
00:21:22.468 --> 00:21:24.637
Is that what your father told you to say?

319
00:21:29.396 --> 00:21:30.856
What did your mother tell you?

320
00:21:32.700 --> 00:21:35.828
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

321
00:21:39.668 --> 00:21:41.145
(Sighs)

322
00:21:41.238 --> 00:21:44.051
(Pensive music playing)

323
00:22:02.139 --> 00:22:04.076
It bothers you. does it not?

324
00:22:08.925 --> 00:22:10.568
My father is a king.

325
00:22:11.224 --> 00:22:14.193
It is his duty to take a new wife
and strengthen his line.

326
00:22:14.278 --> 00:22:15.584
I did not ask for a lesson in politics.

327
00:22:15.669 --> 00:22:17.029
I asked whether this bothers you.

328
00:22:17.114 --> 00:22:18.179
Laena is your daughter. Princess.

329
00:22:18.263 --> 00:22:19.931
Does it bother you?

330
00:22:21.193 --> 00:22:22.319
Of course. it does.

331
00:22:24.222 --> 00:22:26.545
But I understand the order of things.

332
00:22:28.943 --> 00:22:30.600
I'm not sure you do.

333
00:22:33.623 --> 00:22:36.709
If you mean to elicit some anger from me.

334
00:22:36.915 --> 00:22:39.668
you should know that
you're failing. Princess.

335
00:22:40.476 --> 00:22:42.019
Quite the opposite.

336
00:22:45.177 --> 00:22:46.976
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

337
00:22:47.060 --> 00:22:49.979
your father will remarry sooner than late.

338
00:22:50.718 --> 00:22:53.061
His new wife will produce new heirs.

339
00:22:53.146 --> 00:22:55.748
and chances are better than not
that one of those will be male.

340
00:22:55.881 --> 00:22:58.584
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

341
00:22:58.669 --> 00:23:01.217
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

342
00:23:01.302 --> 00:23:02.636
not you.

343
00:23:05.103 --> 00:23:07.022
Because that is the order of things.

344
00:23:09.207 --> 00:23:11.233
When I'm Queen. I will create a new order.

345
00:23:11.403 --> 00:23:12.780
(Princess Rhaenys chuckles)

346
00:23:13.008 --> 00:23:15.135
How I wish that could be. Rhaenyra.

347
00:23:15.839 --> 00:23:18.341
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

348
00:23:18.426 --> 00:23:20.553
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

349
00:23:20.638 --> 00:23:22.139
and they denied it.

350
00:23:22.257 --> 00:23:25.134
They denied you. Princess Rhaenys.

351
00:23:26.088 --> 00:23:28.049
"The Queen Who Never Was."

352
00:23:28.227 --> 00:23:31.022
But they bent the knee to me
and called me heir to the throne.

353
00:23:31.138 --> 00:23:34.100
Do you remind your father's men of that
as you carry their cups?

354
00:23:38.452 --> 00:23:40.412
Here is the hard truth.

355
00:23:40.496 --> 00:23:43.092
which no one else has
the heart to tell you.

356
00:23:44.087 --> 00:23:47.193
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

357
00:23:47.668 --> 00:23:50.497
than see a woman ascend the Iron Throne.

358
00:23:51.987 --> 00:23:54.316
(Tense music playing)

359
00:23:55.335 --> 00:23:57.905
And your father is no fool.

360
00:24:10.831 --> 00:24:13.787
King Viserys: The Small Council
is urging me to remarry.

361
00:24:16.184 --> 00:24:18.506
It seems the realm wants for a new queen.

362
00:24:23.714 --> 00:24:26.584
A good and kind queen
will give comfort to your subjects.

363
00:24:31.860 --> 00:24:34.967
Does the Small Council
have a particular lady in mind?

364
00:24:37.075 --> 00:24:40.920
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

365
00:24:41.752 --> 00:24:43.295
the Lady Laena.

366
00:24:44.343 --> 00:24:46.262
A very strong match. Your Grace.

367
00:24:47.507 --> 00:24:51.311
I must admit.
I don't know Laena very well.

368
00:24:51.819 --> 00:24:54.155
I'm sure that she is good and kind.

369
00:24:54.240 --> 00:24:57.785
and that she will enjoy your company.
as I have. Your Grace.

370
00:25:12.661 --> 00:25:14.204
I brought you something.

371
00:25:33.796 --> 00:25:35.839
I asked the stonemasons to mend it.

372
00:25:36.103 --> 00:25:38.103
(Chuckles)

373
00:25:39.646 --> 00:25:41.607
This is. um.

374
00:25:41.973 --> 00:25:44.767
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

375
00:25:48.730 --> 00:25:50.649
- Very kind.
- (knocking on door)

376
00:25:57.031 --> 00:25:58.117
Come.

377
00:25:58.201 --> 00:25:59.898
(Door opens)

378
00:26:01.382 --> 00:26:03.509
Harrold: The Hand. Your Grace.

379
00:26:05.264 --> 00:26:06.843
(Door closes)

380
00:26:07.696 --> 00:26:11.074
Your Grace. I've called the Small Council
to an emergency session.

381
00:26:11.158 --> 00:26:12.188
Why?

382
00:26:13.166 --> 00:26:15.501
I think it best you hear it directly.

383
00:26:16.598 --> 00:26:17.922
Very well.

384
00:26:18.975 --> 00:26:20.506
(Door opens)

385
00:26:21.818 --> 00:26:23.428
(Door closes

386
00:26:47.719 --> 00:26:50.961
- Daemon.
- The Prince left a missive.

387
00:26:51.046 --> 00:26:52.486
which I believe might explain.

388
00:26:53.422 --> 00:26:56.211
"It is the pleasure of Daemon Targaryen.

389
00:26:56.296 --> 00:26:58.086
"the Prince of Dragons tone

390
00:26:58.171 --> 00:27:01.735
"and rightful heir to the Iron Throne.

391
00:27:01.820 --> 00:27:04.594
"to announce that he is
to take a second wife

392
00:27:04.679 --> 00:27:07.382
"in the tradition of Old Valyria.

393
00:27:07.467 --> 00:27:11.992
"She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragons tone.

394
00:27:12.219 --> 00:27:14.180
"Her Grace is with child

395
00:27:14.265 --> 00:27:19.297
"and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

396
00:27:19.382 --> 00:27:22.280
in the custom of House Targaryen."

397
00:27:22.569 --> 00:27:26.726
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

398
00:27:26.922 --> 00:27:30.175
- It is in two days' time.
- Gods be good.

399
00:27:30.260 --> 00:27:32.262
Who is Lady Mysaria?

400
00:27:32.347 --> 00:27:34.234
- We believe...
- Daemon's whore.

401
00:27:36.246 --> 00:27:39.415
- This is nothing less than sedition.
- I strongly agree. sire.

402
00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:41.627
My brother wishes to provoke me.

403
00:27:42.115 --> 00:27:44.075
To answer is to give him what he wants.

404
00:27:44.160 --> 00:27:46.453
The realm is watching. Your Grace.

405
00:27:46.538 --> 00:27:47.961
King Viserys:
What would you have me do?

406
00:27:48.045 --> 00:27:49.963
Send him to the Wall?

407
00:27:50.410 --> 00:27:52.411
Perhaps I could put his head on a spike.

408
00:27:52.496 --> 00:27:54.523
Otto: Daemon has seized Dragons tone.

409
00:27:54.608 --> 00:27:57.226
has surrounded himself
with an army of gold cloaks.

410
00:27:57.311 --> 00:27:59.343
and has now stolen a dangerous weapon.

411
00:27:59.428 --> 00:28:01.428
(Speaking High Valyrian)
Which egg...

412
00:28:03.637 --> 00:28:05.748
Which egg did Daemon take?

413
00:28:12.612 --> 00:28:16.561
The egg was Dreamfyre's princess.

414
00:28:18.231 --> 00:28:22.866
The samo one you chose
for prince Baelon's cradle.

415
00:28:25.859 --> 00:28:27.861
Assemble a detachment. Otto.

416
00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:31.257
I will go to Dragons tone
and drag Daemon back

417
00:28:31.342 --> 00:28:33.636
- to face justice myself.
- Otto: Your Grace.

418
00:28:34.202 --> 00:28:36.624
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

419
00:28:36.709 --> 00:28:37.882
It's too dangerous.

420
00:28:37.968 --> 00:28:40.062
Daemon is without limit.

421
00:28:40.710 --> 00:28:42.796
Let me go to Dragons tone.

422
00:28:43.107 --> 00:28:46.278
(Pensive music playing)

423
00:28:59.406 --> 00:29:01.406
(Otto sighs)

424
00:29:08.709 --> 00:29:11.491
You're the most comely girl at court.

425
00:29:11.843 --> 00:29:13.970
Why do you destroy yourself?

426
00:29:20.033 --> 00:29:22.160
Will you see the King tonight?

427
00:29:24.942 --> 00:29:26.276
If you wish it.

428
00:29:29.585 --> 00:29:32.194
- Good day. Ser Criston.
- My Lady.

429
00:29:32.395 --> 00:29:35.382
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

430
00:29:35.577 --> 00:29:37.594
Sir Harrold will also join us.

431
00:29:38.348 --> 00:29:40.809
(Tense music playing)

432
00:29:41.639 --> 00:29:44.559
Alicent: Please look after the Hand.
Ser Criston.

433
00:29:51.369 --> 00:29:53.861
(Waves crashing)

434
00:30:16.761 --> 00:30:20.377
(Footsteps approaching)

435
00:31:01.265 --> 00:31:03.648
Welcome to Dragons tone. Otto.

436
00:31:05.632 --> 00:31:08.635
Otto: Your occupation of this island
is at an end.

437
00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:11.562
You're to relinquish the dragon's egg.

438
00:31:11.647 --> 00:31:13.106
disband your army.

439
00:31:13.191 --> 00:31:14.984
banish your whore.

440
00:31:15.938 --> 00:31:18.640
and leave Dragons tone
by order of His Grace.

441
00:31:18.733 --> 00:31:21.151
- King Viserys.
- Where is the King? I don't see him.

442
00:31:21.236 --> 00:31:25.032
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

443
00:31:29.741 --> 00:31:31.409
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

444
00:31:31.494 --> 00:31:33.037
Ser Criston Cole:
Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

445
00:31:33.121 --> 00:31:35.207
Yes. apologies. I couldn't recall.

446
00:31:35.416 --> 00:31:38.366
Perhaps my Prince recalls
when I knocked him off his horse.

447
00:31:39.072 --> 00:31:41.124
(Chuckles) Very good.

448
00:31:41.209 --> 00:31:43.851
Otto: This is a truly pathetic show.
Daemon.

449
00:31:44.033 --> 00:31:45.929
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

450
00:31:46.014 --> 00:31:48.890
that you've resorted to skulking about
like a common cut purse?

451
00:31:48.975 --> 00:31:51.124
I'm simply keeping with
the traditions of my house.

452
00:31:51.209 --> 00:31:52.680
the same as my brother did for his heir.

453
00:31:52.764 --> 00:31:55.749
Those traditions are for the true born
children of royalty.

454
00:31:55.834 --> 00:31:58.545
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

455
00:31:58.945 --> 00:32:00.905
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

456
00:32:00.990 --> 00:32:02.257
Otto: This is an abomination.

457
00:32:02.342 --> 00:32:04.241
With every breath you soil your name.

458
00:32:04.326 --> 00:32:06.119
your house. and your brother's reign.

459
00:32:06.204 --> 00:32:08.640
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

460
00:32:10.108 --> 00:32:12.402
And what of you. men of the City Watch?

461
00:32:12.487 --> 00:32:14.312
Aiding the Prince in his treason?

462
00:32:14.412 --> 00:32:16.110
Prince Daemon:
The King made me their commander.

463
00:32:16.194 --> 00:32:17.678
They are loyal to me.

464
00:32:18.197 --> 00:32:20.116
You've come for the egg.

465
00:32:21.501 --> 00:32:22.752
Here it is.

466
00:32:24.050 --> 00:32:25.927
Are you mad?

467
00:32:26.012 --> 00:32:28.764
- You'd never survive this.
- Well. happily. neither would you.

468
00:32:29.718 --> 00:32:34.597
To chose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

469
00:32:34.682 --> 00:32:35.808
Wonderful.

470
00:32:37.050 --> 00:32:40.800
Even if it ends in the death
of your unborn child and its mother?

471
00:32:47.641 --> 00:32:49.409
(Rumbling)

472
00:32:49.704 --> 00:32:52.730
(Screeching)
(rumbling)

473
00:32:53.718 --> 00:32:55.221
(Roars)

474
00:33:07.655 --> 00:33:11.210
(Caraxes grumbling)

475
00:33:17.620 --> 00:33:18.746
All of you.

476
00:33:19.357 --> 00:33:21.276
sheathe the fucking steel.

477
00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:29.302
(Distant dragon rumbling)

478
00:33:39.490 --> 00:33:41.641
(Wings flapping)

479
00:33:42.048 --> 00:33:44.076
(Syrax screeching)

480
00:34:01.612 --> 00:34:03.612
(Roars)

481
00:34:06.004 --> 00:34:08.257
(Dragons screeching)

482
00:34:25.663 --> 00:34:28.551
- What are you doing here. Princess?
- Preventing bloodshed.

483
00:34:28.636 --> 00:34:31.422
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

484
00:34:31.683 --> 00:34:33.828
Take care not to startle Syrax. my lords.

485
00:34:34.085 --> 00:34:36.203
She's rather protective of me.

486
00:34:36.951 --> 00:34:37.975
{\an8}(Speaking High Valyrian)

487
00:34:38.060 --> 00:34:42.358
- (Waves crashing)
- My father named me princess of Dragonstone.

488
00:34:42.636 --> 00:34:46.675
This is my castle you're living in. uncle.

489
00:34:46.760 --> 00:34:48.905
Not until you come of age.

490
00:34:48.989 --> 00:34:51.186
You have angered your king.

491
00:34:51.270 --> 00:34:53.270
I don't see why?

492
00:34:53.354 --> 00:34:55.686
This is a day of celebration.
I am to be wed.

493
00:34:55.771 --> 00:34:57.155
You already have a wife.

494
00:34:57.246 --> 00:34:59.139
No one of my choosing.

495
00:34:59.957 --> 00:35:04.553
And this required you
to steel my brother a egg?

496
00:35:04.637 --> 00:35:09.464
You shared your cradle with a dragon.
when you were born.

497
00:35:10.342 --> 00:35:12.116
You're to have a child.

498
00:35:14.363 --> 00:35:15.889
One day.

499
00:35:24.182 --> 00:35:26.289
I'm right here. Uncle.

500
00:35:28.218 --> 00:35:30.137
the object of your ire.

501
00:35:30.819 --> 00:35:33.547
the reason that you were disinherited.

502
00:35:33.803 --> 00:35:36.096
If you wish to be restored as heir.

503
00:35:36.180 --> 00:35:37.724
you'll need to kill me.

504
00:35:38.673 --> 00:35:39.844
So. do it.

505
00:35:40.956 --> 00:35:43.033
And be done with all this bother.

506
00:36:08.289 --> 00:36:10.929
(Footsteps departing)

507
00:36:22.549 --> 00:36:26.015
(Intense music playing)

508
00:36:27.220 --> 00:36:29.460
(Vocalizing)

509
00:36:38.064 --> 00:36:40.150
(Syrax screeches)

510
00:36:40.751 --> 00:36:45.298
(Grumbles. roars)

511
00:36:47.389 --> 00:36:51.384
(Triumphant music swells)

512
00:37:12.263 --> 00:37:14.717
(Wind blowing)

513
00:37:23.008 --> 00:37:26.064
(Metal clinking)

514
00:37:31.283 --> 00:37:34.119
Lady Mysaria: You announced
that we were to be wed?

515
00:37:35.128 --> 00:37:36.671
On the morrow.

516
00:37:38.043 --> 00:37:39.962
And that I was with child.

517
00:37:40.894 --> 00:37:42.478
Your child.

518
00:37:42.563 --> 00:37:45.816
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

519
00:37:45.901 --> 00:37:49.673
I ensured long ago that I would never be
threatened by childbirth.

520
00:37:49.758 --> 00:37:52.532
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

521
00:37:52.617 --> 00:37:55.203
You swore to protect me. Daemon.

522
00:37:56.997 --> 00:37:59.124
Dragons tone is quite secure.

523
00:38:01.029 --> 00:38:04.673
Until the King decides to reclaim
his ancestral seat.

524
00:38:05.531 --> 00:38:08.283
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

525
00:38:08.368 --> 00:38:10.620
but what would they do
with the common whore

526
00:38:10.705 --> 00:38:13.103
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

527
00:38:13.188 --> 00:38:14.731
No one will harm you.

528
00:38:15.459 --> 00:38:19.704
I have been sold as property
more times than I care to count.

529
00:38:19.792 --> 00:38:23.212
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

530
00:38:24.394 --> 00:38:27.731
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

531
00:38:28.208 --> 00:38:30.210
You're safe with me. I swear it.

532
00:38:30.295 --> 00:38:31.782
You are Targaryen.

533
00:38:31.949 --> 00:38:35.071
You can afford to play
your stupid games with the King.

534
00:38:35.156 --> 00:38:37.074
but I cannot.

535
00:38:37.878 --> 00:38:41.845
I didn't come into your service
wanting gold or power

536
00:38:42.086 --> 00:38:43.923
or station.

537
00:38:44.463 --> 00:38:48.217
- I came to you to be liberated.
- Liberated.

538
00:38:51.181 --> 00:38:52.349
From what?

539
00:38:53.659 --> 00:38:54.785
Fear.

540
00:38:57.866 --> 00:39:00.471
(Pensive music playing)

541
00:39:19.445 --> 00:39:20.742
(Door closes)

542
00:39:20.943 --> 00:39:22.611
No. please. Lord Lyonel.

543
00:39:28.249 --> 00:39:30.827
I have come looking for
an unencumbered opinion.

544
00:39:30.939 --> 00:39:33.400
That's all I would ever give. Your Grace.

545
00:39:34.094 --> 00:39:37.491
Ever since my name was read
by the archmaesters at the Great Council.

546
00:39:37.590 --> 00:39:40.968
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

547
00:39:41.053 --> 00:39:42.596
from across the Blackwater.

548
00:39:43.249 --> 00:39:46.350
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

549
00:39:46.722 --> 00:39:49.057
Proud men don't like having to look up.

550
00:39:52.772 --> 00:39:54.733
Laena Velaryon.

551
00:39:56.026 --> 00:39:58.733
Lord Corlys is your Master of Ships

552
00:39:59.268 --> 00:40:03.063
and she is the eldest daughter
of the wealthiest house in the realm.

553
00:40:03.148 --> 00:40:06.717
She comes from
unimpeachable Valyrian stock

554
00:40:06.804 --> 00:40:09.311
and she has Targaryen blood.

555
00:40:09.396 --> 00:40:12.006
- What's to mislike?
- She is 12.

556
00:40:12.180 --> 00:40:13.723
She will mature.

557
00:40:16.181 --> 00:40:17.766
I never asked to remarry.

558
00:40:18.350 --> 00:40:21.478
As King. you have a claim on all things.

559
00:40:22.258 --> 00:40:23.717
Even those you don't want.

560
00:40:23.802 --> 00:40:26.460
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

561
00:40:26.545 --> 00:40:29.172
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

562
00:40:29.302 --> 00:40:31.555
He would not be like to take it well.

563
00:40:32.076 --> 00:40:35.872
I fear nothing short of a direct line
to the Iron Throne would satisfy him.

564
00:40:36.300 --> 00:40:39.085
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

565
00:40:39.170 --> 00:40:41.608
on the precipice of war in the Step stones.

566
00:40:42.003 --> 00:40:44.922
And the Sea Snake holds claim to nearly
half the realm's ships.

567
00:40:45.061 --> 00:40:48.197
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

568
00:40:49.250 --> 00:40:52.845
- Who is he to hector me?
- No one. Your Grace.

569
00:40:54.039 --> 00:40:58.043
But Driftmark makes for a better ally
than it does an enemy.

570
00:40:59.106 --> 00:41:01.622
The Sea Snake has made a calculated reach.

571
00:41:01.707 --> 00:41:03.935
a fair play for a man of his position.

572
00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:08.244
If you truly want my unencumbered opinion.

573
00:41:08.329 --> 00:41:09.330
I do.

574
00:41:10.436 --> 00:41:12.948
You should wed Laena Velaryon. Your Grace.

575
00:41:13.635 --> 00:41:16.979
Sate Lord Corlys and fix him at your side.

576
00:41:17.064 --> 00:41:19.103
- permanently. as an ally.
- (door opens)

577
00:41:23.245 --> 00:41:24.621
Ser Steffon Darklyn: Your Grace.

578
00:41:24.705 --> 00:41:27.707
the Princess has returned
from Dragons tone.

579
00:41:27.791 --> 00:41:28.941
Dragons tone?

580
00:41:29.026 --> 00:41:31.043
(Tense music playing)

581
00:41:31.206 --> 00:41:34.544
(Vocalizing)

582
00:41:48.352 --> 00:41:49.478
Your Grace.

583
00:41:53.389 --> 00:41:55.448
King Viserys: You disobeyed me.

584
00:41:55.533 --> 00:41:58.737
You fled King's Landing without a word

585
00:41:59.478 --> 00:42:02.893
and you acted without The Crown's leave.

586
00:42:05.896 --> 00:42:08.064
You are my only heir.

587
00:42:09.106 --> 00:42:11.024
You could've been killed.

588
00:42:14.574 --> 00:42:15.950
May I sit?

589
00:42:26.904 --> 00:42:28.932
You went to Dragons tone.

590
00:42:29.173 --> 00:42:31.245
And retrieved the egg without bloodshed.

591
00:42:33.326 --> 00:42:36.454
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

592
00:42:39.355 --> 00:42:41.575
Yes. well.
(chuckles)

593
00:42:45.797 --> 00:42:48.555
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

594
00:42:51.405 --> 00:42:52.671
(Sighs)

595
00:42:58.047 --> 00:43:02.218
Your mother's absence
is a wound that will never heal.

596
00:43:03.456 --> 00:43:04.790
Without her.

597
00:43:05.581 --> 00:43:09.944
the Red Keep has lost a warmth
that I dare say it will never recover.

598
00:43:10.029 --> 00:43:13.157
It pleases me to hear you say this.

599
00:43:16.752 --> 00:43:20.046
To know that I'm not alone in my grief.

600
00:43:20.131 --> 00:43:22.549
I wish I had known better

601
00:43:22.634 --> 00:43:24.845
what to say to you in the aftermath.

602
00:43:27.163 --> 00:43:31.083
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

603
00:43:34.764 --> 00:43:36.307
But I know

604
00:43:36.946 --> 00:43:40.574
she understands
what is now expected of me.

605
00:43:40.783 --> 00:43:43.202
The King must take a new wife.

606
00:43:47.693 --> 00:43:49.820
I could never replace your mother.

607
00:43:52.045 --> 00:43:54.297
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

608
00:43:55.969 --> 00:43:58.137
But you are my only heir

609
00:43:58.222 --> 00:44:01.561
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

610
00:44:01.954 --> 00:44:04.412
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

611
00:44:04.497 --> 00:44:05.740
that we are better defended.

612
00:44:05.825 --> 00:44:06.909
Against whom?

613
00:44:07.064 --> 00:44:09.204
Whomever may dare to challenge us.

614
00:44:15.439 --> 00:44:17.881
I do not wish to make us estranged.

615
00:44:18.682 --> 00:44:20.100
You are the King.

616
00:44:20.668 --> 00:44:24.029
and so. your first duty is to the realm.

617
00:44:27.076 --> 00:44:28.995
Mother would've understood this.

618
00:44:31.408 --> 00:44:32.883
Just as I do.

619
00:44:32.996 --> 00:44:35.952
(Pensive music playing)

620
00:44:37.082 --> 00:44:38.372
(Birds cawing)

621
00:44:38.487 --> 00:44:41.356
(Pensive music playing)

622
00:44:51.172 --> 00:44:52.809
(Door opens)

623
00:44:56.718 --> 00:44:58.718
(Indistinct chatter)

624
00:45:14.316 --> 00:45:16.316
(Door closes)

625
00:45:17.971 --> 00:45:20.010
Good morrow. my lords.

626
00:45:30.713 --> 00:45:34.258
I have decided to take a new wife.

627
00:45:51.630 --> 00:45:53.298
I intend to marry

628
00:45:59.769 --> 00:46:01.854
the Lady Alicent High tower

629
00:46:03.583 --> 00:46:05.502
before spring's end.

630
00:46:11.987 --> 00:46:13.799
This is an absurdity.

631
00:46:14.701 --> 00:46:17.354
My house is Valyrian.

632
00:46:17.439 --> 00:46:19.566
the greatest power in the realm.

633
00:46:20.715 --> 00:46:22.410
And I am your King.

634
00:46:22.518 --> 00:46:24.520
(Tense music playing)

635
00:46:34.964 --> 00:46:36.964
(Door opens)

636
00:46:39.425 --> 00:46:41.425
(Door closes)

637
00:46:46.354 --> 00:46:47.897
King Viserys: Rhaenyra.

638
00:47:09.045 --> 00:47:12.590
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

639
00:47:14.425 --> 00:47:16.970
More ancient even than House Targaryen

640
00:47:18.695 --> 00:47:20.613
according to some texts.

641
00:47:22.201 --> 00:47:24.364
But unlike the Targaryens.

642
00:47:24.808 --> 00:47:26.727
we were no dragon lords.

643
00:47:27.982 --> 00:47:32.277
For centuries. my house had to scratch out
an existence from the sea

644
00:47:32.361 --> 00:47:34.653
with grit and luck.

645
00:47:36.940 --> 00:47:39.200
When I ascended the Driftwood Throne.

646
00:47:40.363 --> 00:47:41.906
I knew what I wanted.

647
00:47:43.727 --> 00:47:45.645
So I went out and seized it.

648
00:47:47.165 --> 00:47:48.773
Unlike every other lord of the realm.

649
00:47:48.858 --> 00:47:51.692
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

650
00:47:51.777 --> 00:47:53.905
with the strength of mine own back.

651
00:47:55.216 --> 00:47:57.216
(Tense music playing)

652
00:48:00.027 --> 00:48:02.528
I've always thought of
you and I as having been

653
00:48:02.670 --> 00:48:04.422
made from the same cloth.

654
00:48:13.087 --> 00:48:15.622
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

655
00:48:15.762 --> 00:48:19.182
We're both men who have had to cut
our own way through the world.

656
00:48:20.105 --> 00:48:23.024
We've been passed over too often.

657
00:48:25.652 --> 00:48:27.090
Did you call me to Driftmark

658
00:48:27.175 --> 00:48:29.239
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

659
00:48:29.324 --> 00:48:31.242
or was there some other reason?

660
00:48:34.740 --> 00:48:36.825
You've heard of the troubles
in the Step stones?

661
00:48:39.664 --> 00:48:43.709
<i>Daemon: Some Myrish Prince
is feeding Westerosi sailors to the crabs.</i>

662
00:48:43.794 --> 00:48:46.598
<i>Corlys: I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy</i>

663
00:48:46.695 --> 00:48:48.405
<i>into the territory.</i>

664
00:48:48.490 --> 00:48:50.153
but he's denied me.

665
00:48:50.238 --> 00:48:52.231
It was never my brother's strongest trait.

666
00:48:52.430 --> 00:48:53.458
What?

667
00:48:54.683 --> 00:48:56.101
Being King.

668
00:49:00.590 --> 00:49:03.138
<i>Corlys: The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities</i>

669
00:49:03.223 --> 00:49:06.184
<i>within the Free Cities who wish to see
Westeros weakened.</i>

670
00:49:06.887 --> 00:49:08.255
(Sailor grunting)

671
00:49:08.340 --> 00:49:11.828
<i>And the King's failures
have allowed him to accumulate strength.</i>

672
00:49:13.588 --> 00:49:16.307
If those shipping lanes fall.

673
00:49:16.429 --> 00:49:18.347
my house will be crippled.

674
00:49:19.141 --> 00:49:21.635
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

675
00:49:21.720 --> 00:49:24.924
idles himself with feasts.
and balls. and tourneys.

676
00:49:25.042 --> 00:49:27.962
I will speak of my brother as I wish.

677
00:49:29.460 --> 00:49:30.961
You will not.

678
00:49:34.523 --> 00:49:36.316
Waiting in the Step stones

679
00:49:36.401 --> 00:49:38.528
is a chance for you to prove your worth

680
00:49:38.613 --> 00:49:40.907
to any who might yet doubt it.

681
00:49:42.090 --> 00:49:44.634
We are the realm's second sons. Daemon.

682
00:49:45.998 --> 00:49:47.917
Our worth is not given.

683
00:49:49.472 --> 00:49:51.391
It must be made.

684
00:49:52.873 --> 00:49:55.597
(Intense music playing)

685
00:49:56.305 --> 00:50:56.657
